President Joseph R. Biden, Jr. and Chancellor Angela Merkel of Germany had a discussion today, where they emphasized their strong commitment to the transatlantic relationship. They pledged to work closely together on various shared priorities, including fighting against COVID-19, strengthening global health security, and addressing the climate crisis. Both leaders expressed concern over the increased presence of Russian troops near Ukraine's borders and in occupied Crimea. They also reaffirmed their support for Ukraine's sovereignty and territorial integrity. President Biden thanked Chancellor Merkel for Germany's contributions to NATO's Resolute Support Mission in Afghanistan, and they both agreed to continue supporting efforts to bring peace to Afghanistan.